- LSTM (Long short-term memory) model is a type of Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) used for predicting stock prices and analyzing time series data; 
- 'Return on Equity' is a KPI calculated as net income divided by shareholder equity, reflecting a company's profitability; 
- 'Debt-to-Equity Ratio' is a KPI calculated as total liabilities divided by shareholder equity, indicating a company's level of indebtedness; 
- Positive or negative sentiment in news feeds can impact stock prices and investor confidence.

- High returns refer to a return on equity (ROE) greater than 20; 
- High confidence levels refer to a confidence score above 0.8; 
- Bullish trends are trends with the name 'Bullish' in the trends table.
